  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I got one year private tutoring from a student who was Jewish and very nice and very patient and was paid for it by my father.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And but then we couldn't-- I obviously could-- my father couldn't afford to continue in that style, and that was that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His health, health problems were internal, and he was classified like for non-immigration.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I imagine that even today with that particular illness-- I mean, he was perfectly fit with a certain problems which could be seen to under normal circumstances.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we found out that in Theresienstadt, even not under normal circumstances, he saw to the problems he had.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it-- he was officially unacceptable to any country for immigration.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
